INSERT INTO `content` (`id`, `objecttype`, `objectid`, `contentcontainer_id`, `content`, `language`, `editable`, `status`) VALUES
(9, 'page', 1, 1, '<h1 style="text-align: center;">SeeCMS - take control of your site</h1>\n<p>SeeCMS lets you add text to your website with ease, ensuring that your brand and style are being honoured at all times. Add headings, sub headings, main content, all in an intuitive way - making website maintenance a pleasure, not a chore.</p>\n<p>Whether you''re a techie or a technophobe, SeeCMS arms you with the tools to add wording that tells your customers and clients who you are, what you do and why visitors should engage with you.</p>\n<p>Your website should work hard for you - bringing in leads, giving useful calls to action and engaging your existing customers.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Take control of your site with SeeCMS.</p>\n', 'en', 1, 1),
(18, 'page', 2, 1, '<h1 style="text-align: center;">Create captivating headings</h1>\n<p>Don''t just call your page ''about us'' - give it a bit of thought. Can you use something more creative, or more pertinent to your business? How about ''getting to know us'' or ''meet the organisation of your dreams''. It''s your site, and you''re in control.</p>\n<p>Sure, use professionals to help you formulate just the right messages if words aren''t you thing. After all, there''s lots to consider - how much text to write, what do you want to get across, what will appeal to your visitors.</p>\n<p>And of course there''s Search Engine Optimisation (SEO) to think about. How do you get those magic keywords across the content without writing something that''s not only hard to read, but obviously written mainly to boost rankings.</p>\n<p>Content is key, or so they say. And to that end, your text should be high-quality, well-written and appealing to visitors. That will show by the length of time people spend on your site and whether they share your content socially - all markers of a good website in the eys of Google (other search engines are available, of course).</p>\n', 'en', 1, 1),
(21, 'page', 7, 2, '<p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat.</p>\n', 'en', 1, 1),
(22, 'page', 6, 2, '<p>If someone has found your website and taken the time to have a little poke around, it needs to be simple for them to go a step further. A lot of the time this call to action is simply to get in touch.</p>\n', 'en', 1, 1),
(23, 'page', 5, 2, '<p>A photo says a thousand words, or so the old addage goes. If top-notch images will help your cause, get them on your site - either within the content, or in the form of a gallery or galleries.</p>\n<p>Thanks to <a href="https://stocksnap.io/">stocksnap.io</a> for the copyright free stock photos.</p>\n', 'en', 1, 1),
(24, 'page', 3, 2, '<p>You''ve won an award, you''ve held a brilliant event, you''ve secured a new contract. Share your news/events with your visitors and you can big yourself up, all in the name of being sociable. Add pictures to your news stories and you''re opening up your organisation, giving it a face. You show yourself as a business worth engaging with, a service great to use.</p>\n', 'en', 1, 1),
(25, 'page', 2, 2, '<p>So you''ve got a website, it looks great and has lots of features. Now you need to get across who you are, what you do, and why people should use you. Use your content wisely and you can get across all of your messages.</p>\n', 'en', 1, 1),
(26, 'page', 8, 2, '<p>Adding further content to your website is simple. Information can get more complex and you can put your point across in more detail. Use your inner pages wisely to build up your content.</p>\n', 'en', 1, 1),
(27, 'page', 9, 2, '<p>Websites can easily grow as you do. It''s simple to add pages to your website packed with useful content as your company or organisation develops.</p>\n', 'en', 1, 1),
(28, 'page', 9, 1, '<h1 style="text-align: center;">Your website can grow as you do</h1>\n<p>When you first go live with a new site, it should be well-organised, feature all of your best photos, your latest projects,and be generally, well, up-to-date.</p>\n<p>But as you carry on doing what you do and the weeks become motnhs become years, your website should be reflecting your progress.</p>\n<p>Whether you expand in size, provide more services or win more clients, there''s potentially more information to add to the website, and whilst it''s easy to add all of your new exciting content, it''s also easy for it to get a bit unweildy.</p>\n<p>Your website needs love, care and attention - and that will please the search engines too, so make sure to give your website a spring clean from time to time, won''t you?</p>\n', 'en', 1, 1),
(29, 'page', 8, 1, '<h1 style="text-align: center;">Add layers to your site (but not too many...)</h1>\n<p>Secondary navigation, and even tertiary navigation, can add layers of information to your website. Hit the visitor with some overarching information on the homepage as a catch all, and then allow your customers to delve as deep as they want to into your site.</p>\n<p>You can add to the levels of complexity the further people journey around your site. But don''t overdo it - content hidden away is less likely to be found, and won''t provide for a great user experience, and you could be missing getting some key information across.</p>\n<p>Three clicks to every piece of information is pretty good practice, but if your site has thousans of pages, that might not be so easy. Make sure to spread your information out, and always consider your site''s architecture.</p>\n', 'en', 1, 1),
