magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat.&nbsp;<br><br></strong></p>\n<table style="height: 78px;" width="687"><tbody><tr><th style="text-align: left;">Table heading</th>\n<th style="text-align: left;">Table heading</th>\n</tr><tr><td>Table text</td>\n<td>Table text</td>\n</tr><tr><td>Table text</td>\n<td>Table text</td>\n</tr><tr><td>Table text</td>\n<td>Table text</td>\n</tr></tbody></table>\n', 'en', 1, 1),
(40, 'post', 3, 1, '<p>SeeCMS was ten years in the making and launched to the world at Venturefest, Yorkshire''s leading science, technology and innovation event.</p>\n<p>Releasing the CMS as an open source product for the first time, we listened to our customers to make sure that we are providing services with them in mind.</p>\n<p>Our content management system is the backbone of hundreds of websites across Yorkshire, the UK and indeed further afield, internationally.</p>\n<p>The move to release SeeCMS as an open source product has come from our passion for providing the best possible service to our clients.</p>\n<p>Director Anne Taylor said: "As a digital agency, we''re always keen to keep ahead of the game, and we''re confident that SeeCMS provides our clients with all of the tools needed to take full control of their websites in an intuitive and informative way."</p>\n', 'en', 1, 1),
(41, 'post', 4, 1, '<p>A news article should be interesting and have a point. It needs to cover some important questions: who, why, what, where and when.</p>\n<p>Who is the article about, why is this newsworthy, what were the subjects doing, where did, or will, the news happen and when.</p>\n<p>From there on in, try to keep in engaging - not too long and not too short. Just right, as Goldilocks would say. Don''t forget to use pictures, link to further information and giving people the chance to comment or share is great.</p>\n', 'en', 1, 1),
(45, 'page', 10, 2, '<p>All kinds of businesses and organisations have an events calendar - schools parents evenings, theatre shows, training sessions, conferences, dinners - the list is pretty endless.</p>\n', 'en', 1, 1),
